FT  12 DEC 94 / Arts (Openings): Leeds
Bayreuth's resident Wotan turns up in a new guise in Leeds on Thursday. As
well as singing the title-role, John Tomlinson will be making his debut as a
director in Opera North's rare production of Verdi's first opera, 'Oberto'.
David Porcelijn is the conductor and the cast also includes Rita Cullis,
Linda Finnie and David Maxwell-Anderson.
